  # Development Cheat Sheet
  
  ## Prerequisites (assume exists)
  - JAVA_HOME set to JDK 21 (GraalVM recommended to match CI)
  - Docker
  - grype v0.104.0 (install: curl -sSfL https://get.anchore.io/grype/v0.104.0/install.sh | sudo sh -s -- -b /usr/local/bin)
  
  ## Setup
  - Always use Gradle wrapper from repo root:
    - Unix: ./gradlew <task> [options]
    - Windows: gradlew.bat <task> [options]
  - Tip: add --stacktrace for debugging
  
  ## One command for complete infrastructure testing
  ./gradlew testAllInfra -Pparallelism=4 --stacktrace
  
  Run the future-defaults lane locally with:
  GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew testAllInfra -Pparallelism=4 --stacktrace
  
  ## Code Style
  - Always try to reuse existing code.
  - Be assertive in code.
  - Write type annotations in all functions and most variables.
  - Document code without being too verbose.
  - In Java and Groovy, always import classes and use them without qualified names.
  - In Java use multi-line strings where possible.
  - In Java use the markdown style for comments.
  
  ## Testing individual components
  
  - Clean previous build outputs for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew clean -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  - Pre-fetch Docker images allowed by metadata (used in tests) for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  - Validate reachability metadata files for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  - Run Checkstyle for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew checkstyle -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  - Compile test sources for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  - Run JVM-based tests for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  - Build native images used by native tests (compile-only) for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew nativeTestCompile -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  - Run all tests for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]
  
  
  ## Check style and formatting
  - Style check: ./gradlew checkstyle
  - Format check: ./gradlew spotlessCheck
  
  ## Testing the metadata
  - Single library (replace with group:artifact:version):
    - ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version
    - ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version
    - ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version
    - GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version
  - Sharded example (1/64):
    - ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=1/64
    - ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=1/64
    - ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=1/64
  
  Metadata CI currently runs both `current-defaults` and `future-defaults-all`.
  
  ### Generating Metadata
  - Generate metadata for a certain library version:
     - ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=com.hazelcast:hazelcast:5.2.1
  - Generate metadata for a certain library version and derive `user-code-filter.json` from the resolved library JAR:
     - ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar
  - Generate metadata for a certain library version and create or update the user-code-filter.json:
     - ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=org.example.app,com.acme.service
  
  ### Fix failing tasks
  
  - Generates new metadata for library's new version which is failing native-image run:
    - ./gradlew fixTestNativeImageRun -PtestLibraryCoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 -PnewLibraryVersion=42.7.4
  
  ## Docker Image Vulnerability Scanning
  - Changed images between commits:
    - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages --baseCommit=$(git rev-parse origin/master) --newCommit=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
  - All allowed images:
    - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages
  
  ## Compatibility Automation (latest library versions)
  - List libs with newer upstream versions:
    - ./gradlew fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions --quiet
  - Record a newly tested version:
    - ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates="group:artifact:newVersion" --lastSupportedVersion="oldVersion"
    - Example: ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates="org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.4" --lastSupportedVersion="42.7.3"
  
  ## Releases and Packaging
  - Package artifacts: ./gradlew package
[recv] {"type": "message_start", "message": {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_wrR139cjoOTngOlKgJjP9NKF|fc_0cb6a61bc62d775f0169ef5c06c77081949ef96de047ed5096", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Development Cheat Sheet\n\n## Prerequisites (assume exists)\n- JAVA_HOME set to JDK 21 (GraalVM recommended to match CI)\n- Docker\n- grype v0.104.0 (install: curl -sSfL https://get.anchore.io/grype/v0.104.0/install.sh | sudo sh -s -- -b /usr/local/bin)\n\n## Setup\n- Always use Gradle wrapper from repo root:\n  - Unix: ./gradlew <task> [options]\n  - Windows: gradlew.bat <task> [options]\n- Tip: add --stacktrace for debugging\n\n## One command for complete infrastructure testing\n./gradlew testAllInfra -Pparallelism=4 --stacktrace\n\nRun the future-defaults lane locally with:\nGVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew testAllInfra -Pparallelism=4 --stacktrace\n\n## Code Style\n- Always try to reuse existing code.\n- Be assertive in code.\n- Write type annotations in all functions and most variables.\n- Document code without being too verbose.\n- In Java and Groovy, always import classes and use them without qualified names.\n- In Java use multi-line strings where possible.\n- In Java use the markdown style for comments.\n\n## Testing individual components\n\n- Clean previous build outputs for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew clean -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n- Pre-fetch Docker images allowed by metadata (used in tests) for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n- Validate reachability metadata files for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n- Run Checkstyle for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew checkstyle -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n- Compile test sources for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n- Run JVM-based tests for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n- Build native images used by native tests (compile-only) for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew nativeTestCompile -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n- Run all tests for the selected coordinates: ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n\n\n## Check style and formatting\n- Style check: ./gradlew checkstyle\n- Format check: ./gradlew spotlessCheck\n\n## Testing the metadata\n- Single library (replace with group:artifact:version):\n  - ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\n  - ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\n  - ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\n  - GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\n- Sharded example (1/64):\n  - ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=1/64\n  - ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=1/64\n  - ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=1/64\n\nMetadata CI currently runs both `current-defaults` and `future-defaults-all`.\n\n### Generating Metadata\n- Generate metadata for a certain library version:\n   - ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=com.hazelcast:hazelcast:5.2.1\n- Generate metadata for a certain library version and derive `user-code-filter.json` from the resolved library JAR:\n   - ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\n- Generate metadata for a certain library version and create or update the user-code-filter.json:\n   - ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=org.example.app,com.acme.service\n\n### Fix failing tasks\n\n- Generates new metadata for library's new version which is failing native-image run:\n  - ./gradlew fixTestNativeImageRun -PtestLibraryCoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 -PnewLibraryVersion=42.7.4\n\n## Docker Image Vulnerability Scanning\n- Changed images between commits:\n  - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages --baseCommit=$(git rev-parse origin/master) --newCommit=$(git rev-parse HEAD)\n- All allowed images:\n  - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages\n\n## Compatibility Automation (latest library versions)\n- List libs with newer upstream versions:\n  - ./gradlew fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions --quiet\n- Record a newly tested version:\n  - ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\"group:artifact:newVersion\" --lastSupportedVersion=\"oldVersion\"\n  - Example: ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\"org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.4\" --lastSupportedVersion=\"42.7.3\"\n\n## Releases and Packaging\n- Package artifacts: ./gradlew package\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777294344677}}
